FBIS3-38861 "drweu027aa_94024" FBIS-WEU-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Hague Court Backs Chad in Dispute With Libya LD0402125794 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 4 Feb 94 LD0402125794 Hilversum Radio Netherlands Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The International Court of Justice in The Hague has ruled in Chad's favor in its border conflict with Libya. The ruling means that Libya, which has controllled the disputed territory since 1973, must now evacuate the area. Chad and Libya have fought two wars over the land, which is the size of France and thought to be rich in uranium and oil. In 1990 the two countries agreed to put the issue before the International Court, pledging to accept its ruling.
